He made large endowments on both of these churches out of his own domains, and devoutly assisted at the celebration of the holy mysteries.
Maurilius, archbishop of Rouen, with his suffragan bishops, humbly and reverently performed the consecration, and shortly afterwards took to his bed in the twelfth year of his episcopate.
Having fulfilled all the duties of a devout servant of God, he departed to him whom he had long served on the 5th of the ides [9th] of August.
His body was conveyed to the cathedral church, which five years before [the first indiction] he had dedicated to St. Mary, mother of God, and it was there interred with high honours before the crucifix.
